The marriage of a daughter of Michael IX Palaiologos and his wife Rita of Armenia to a Georgian ruler is not recorded in Byzantine sources. Neither is the existence of any illegitimate daughters of Michael IX.[1] The Komnenoi did rule however in the Empire of Trebizond. A Michael Komnenos was Emperor from 1344 to 1349. His wife was Acropolitissa. Their only child recorded in primary sources was John III of Trebizond. Whether John III had siblings is unknown.' I just made up the possible sibling.

	1204.4.12 = { #He technically died in December but if he's alive it breaks the decision to to restore the ERE in the 1204 bookmark and if I use holder = 0 ports over the 'destroyed' part to all the titles when I use insert_title_history which I try to avoid. Alexios was never going to reclaim the throne anyway so just going to kill him off when he lost the throne.
		death = {
			death_reason=death_execution
		}
	}
}
